{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexCompileFlags"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/regexcompileflags\/dollarendonly"]}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A dollar metacharacter (”$”) in the pattern"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"matches only at the end of the string. Without this option, a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"dollar also matches immediately before the final character if","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it is a newline (but not before any other newlines). This option"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is ignored if "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexCompileFlags\/multiline","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" is set.","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"let","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"dollarEndonly","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib17RegexCompileFlagsV","text":"RegexCompileFlags","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexCompileFlags"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexCompileFlags\/dollarEndonly"},"metadata":{"symbolKind":"property","title":"dollarEndonly","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"roleHeading":"Type Property","fragments":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"let","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"dollarEndonly"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib17RegexCompileFlagsV","text":"RegexCompileFlags"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib17RegexCompileFlagsV13dollarEndonlyACvpZ","role":"symbol"},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/RegexCompileFlags":{"role":"symbol","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Flags specifying compile-time options.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"RegexCompileFlags","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"RegexCompileFlags","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/regexcompileflags","title":"RegexCompileFlags","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexCompileFlags"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"abstract":[],"kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/glib","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/RegexCompileFlags/dollarEndonly":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/regexcompileflags\/dollarendonly","title":"dollarEndonly","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexCompileFlags\/dollarEndonly","fragments":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"let","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"dollarEndonly","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"RegexCompileFlags","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib17RegexCompileFlagsV","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A dollar metacharacter (”$”) in the pattern"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"matches only at the end of the string. Without this option, a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"dollar also matches immediately before the final character if"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"it is a newline (but not before any other newlines). This option"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is ignored if "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexCompileFlags\/multiline","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is set."}],"role":"symbol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/RegexCompileFlags/multiline":{"title":"multiline","fragments":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"let","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"multiline"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"RegexCompileFlags","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib17RegexCompileFlagsV"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"By default, GRegex treats the strings as consisting"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of a single line of characters (even if it actually contains"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"newlines). The “start of line” metacharacter (”^”) matches only"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"at the start of the string, while the “end of line” metacharacter"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(”$”) matches only at the end of the string, or before a terminating","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"newline (unless "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexCompileFlags\/dollarEndonly","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" is set). When"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexCompileFlags\/multiline"},{"text":" is set, the “start of line” and “end of line”","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"constructs match immediately following or immediately before any","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"newline in the string, respectively, as well as at the very start"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and end. This can be changed within a pattern by a “(?m)” option"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"setting.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/regexcompileflags\/multiline","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexCompileFlags\/multiline"}}}